<subSubSection id="C32845C11A61FFFED2AB0A98FEBBF954" pageId="63" pageNumber="374" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8D164A1A61FFFED2AB0A98FCD8FBE8" blockId="63.[211,1444,1009,1134]" pageId="63" pageNumber="374">
Espèce très grêle, de teinte claire uniforme, à large répartition en Afrique, déjà signalée du 
<collectingRegion id="49F6D8A81A61FFFED6DC0A98FB58FB8E" box="[1157,1227,1009,1032]" country="Liberia" name="Nimba" pageId="63" pageNumber="374">Nimba</collectingRegion>
par 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA36BBB1A61FFFED6A10A98FE97FBAC" author="CHOPARD L." pageId="63" pageNumber="374" pagination="127 - 153" refId="ref40676" refString="CHOPARD L. 1958. - Acridiens, in La Reserve naturelle integrale du Mont Nimba, IV. Memoires de l'Institut francais d'Afrique noire 53: 127 - 153." type="journal article" year="1958">Chopard (1958: 147)</bibRefCitation>
sous le nom de 
<taxonomicName id="4C326DC91A61FFFED3E90D7AFD79FBAC" authority="(Krauss, 1877)" baseAuthorityName="Krauss" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[432,746,1043,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Mesopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilicornis">
<emphasis id="B946CA581A61FFFED3E90D7AFDD5FBAC" box="[432,582,1043,1066]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="374">M. gracilicornis</emphasis>
(Krauss, 1877)
</taxonomicName>
, espèce mise en synonymie d’ 
<taxonomicName id="4C326DC91A61FFFED6780D7AFB03FBAC" authorityName="¢ Kirby" authorityYear="1910" box="[1057,1168,1043,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Mesopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abbreviatus">
<emphasis id="B946CA581A61FFFED6780D7AFB03FBAC" box="[1057,1168,1043,1066]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="374">abbreviatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
par 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA36BBB1A61FFFED6990D7AFA15FBAC" author="DIRSH V. M." box="[1216,1414,1043,1066]" pageId="63" pageNumber="374" refId="ref40798" refString="DIRSH V. M. 1966. - Acridoidea of Angola. Publicacoes culturais de Companhia de Diamantes de Angola 74: 527 p." type="book" year="1966">Dirsh (1966: 464)</bibRefCitation>
, et signalée aussi par 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA36BBB1A61FFFED3D20D5CFDD9FBCA" author="DIRSH V. M." box="[395,586,1077,1100]" pageId="63" pageNumber="374" pagination="207 - 220" refId="ref40739" refString="DIRSH V. M. 1963. - Orthoptera Acridoidea (Second contribution), in La Reserve naturelle integrale du Mont Nimba, V. Memoires de l'Institut francais d'Afrique noire 66: 207 - 220." type="journal article" year="1963">Dirsh (1963: 219)</bibRefCitation>
sous le nom erroné de 
<taxonomicName id="4C326DC91A61FFFED1610D5CFBF6FBCA" authority="Chopard, 1958" authorityName="Chopard" authorityYear="1958" box="[824,1125,1077,1100]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Nimbacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis">
<emphasis id="B946CA581A61FFFED1610D5CFC53FBCA" box="[824,960,1077,1100]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="374">M. longicornis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA36BBB1A61FFFED19F0D5CFBF6FBCA" author="CHOPARD L." box="[966,1125,1077,1100]" pageId="63" pageNumber="374" pagination="127 - 153" refId="ref40676" refString="CHOPARD L. 1958. - Acridiens, in La Reserve naturelle integrale du Mont Nimba, IV. Memoires de l'Institut francais d'Afrique noire 53: 127 - 153." type="journal article" year="1958">Chopard, 1958</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, qui est en réalité synonyme de l’espèce suivante. 
<collectingRegion id="49F6D8A81A61FFFED3D20D3EFE3EFBE8" box="[395,429,1111,1134]" country="Cameroon" name="East" pageId="63" pageNumber="374">Les</collectingRegion>
nouvelles captures ont été nombreuses.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8D164A1A61FFFED3880CE6FB1DFA38" blockId="63.[465,1191,1423,1470]" pageId="63" pageNumber="374">
<emphasis id="B946CA581A61FFFED3880CE6FD81FA26" bold="true" box="[465,530,1423,1440]" pageId="63" pageNumber="374">FIG. 28.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C326DC91A61FFFED04E0CE6FC85FA26" authority="(Beauvoir)" baseAuthorityName="Beauvoir" box="[535,790,1423,1440]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Mesopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abbreviatus">
<emphasis id="B946CA581A61FFFED04E0CE6FD2CFA26" box="[535,703,1423,1440]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="374">Mesopsis abbreviatus</emphasis>
(Beauvoir)
</taxonomicName>
, femelle, longueur 
<quantity id="4CCABBAF1A61FFFED1F70CE6FC74FA26" box="[942,999,1423,1440]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.4" pageId="63" pageNumber="374" unit="mm" value="64.0">64 mm</quantity>
; d’après 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA36BBB1A61FFFED66F0CE6FB30FA26" author="MESTRE J." box="[1078,1187,1423,1440]" pageId="63" pageNumber="374" refId="ref42085" refString="MESTRE J. 1988. - Les Acridiens des formations herbeuses d'Afrique de l'Ouest. Ministere de la Cooperation, Paris; CIRAD-GERDAT-PRIFAS, Montpellier, 332 p." type="book" year="1988">Mestre, 1988</bibRefCitation>
. 
<emphasis id="B946CA581A61FFFED3B20CC4FDB8FA38" bold="true" box="[491,555,1453,1470]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="374">FIG. 28.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C326DC91A61FFFED0690CC4FCBDFA38" authority="(Beauvoir)" baseAuthorityName="Beauvoir" box="[560,814,1453,1470]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Mesopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abbreviatus">
Mesopsis abbreviatus 
<emphasis id="B946CA581A61FFFED0870CC4FCBDFA38" box="[734,814,1453,1470]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="374">(Beauvoir)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B946CA581A61FFFED1770CC4FB1DFA38" box="[814,1166,1453,1470]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="374">
, female, length 
<quantity id="4CCABBAF1A61FFFED1F60CC4FC74FA38" box="[943,999,1453,1470]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.4" pageId="63" pageNumber="374" unit="mm" value="64.0">64 mm</quantity>
; after 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA36BBB1A61FFFED6440CC4FB19FA38" author="MESTRE J." box="[1053,1162,1453,1470]" pageId="63" pageNumber="374" refId="ref42085" refString="MESTRE J. 1988. - Les Acridiens des formations herbeuses d'Afrique de l'Ouest. Ministere de la Cooperation, Paris; CIRAD-GERDAT-PRIFAS, Montpellier, 332 p." type="book" year="1988">Mestre, 1988</bibRefCitation>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8D164A1A61FFFED2AB0F79FD84F908" blockId="63.[211,1444,1552,1746]" pageId="63" pageNumber="374">
L’espèce est surtout fréquente en savane (Ziéla, Kéoulenta, Gbakoré, Séringbara, plateau de Zouguépo 
<quantity id="4CCABBAF1A61FFFED7560F79FA10F9A1" box="[1295,1411,1552,1575]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.7" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.4" pageId="63" pageNumber="374" unit="m" value="770.0" valueMax="800.0" valueMin="740.0">740-800 m</quantity>
) et relativement abondante aussi en prairie sur cuirasse (près Gbakoré, Niomouya, plateau de Zouguépo 
<quantity id="4CCABBAF1A61FFFED6840F5BFAB1F9CF" box="[1245,1314,1586,1609]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.2" pageId="63" pageNumber="374" unit="m" value="720.0">720 m</quantity>
); également de rares captures en prairie d’altitude (plateau de Zouguépo 
<quantity id="4CCABBAF1A61FFFED1620F3CFC1DF9EA" box="[827,910,1621,1644]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="63" pageNumber="374" unit="m" value="1100.0">1100 m</quantity>
, Pierré Richaud, au voisinage du camp 
<quantity id="4CCABBAF1A61FFFED7790F3CFA04F9EA" box="[1312,1431,1621,1644]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.004999999999999" metricValueMax="16.0" metricValueMin="0.01" pageId="63" pageNumber="374" unit="m" value="800.5" valueMax="1600.0" valueMin="1.0">1 à 1600 m</quantity>
), aucune dans les autres milieux.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8D164A1A61FFFED2AB0FF0FEBBF954" blockId="63.[211,1444,1552,1746]" pageId="63" pageNumber="374">Des adultes et des jeunes à divers stades ont été trouvés d’août à mars, tandis qu’aucune capture n’est à signaler d’avril à juillet.</paragraph>
